Hi everyone!

It has been a while! I didn’t mean to go on this long of a hiatus, but (and excuse me for using this phrase for the dozenth time) these past few months have been a whirlwind. I hope you all are well.

For those of you who are wondering, I’m still booking and will be until I announce otherwise! I have a few more slots available in Dallas (December-January and May onwards) as well as in Austin (January-April).

My activity on this account may be a bit sporadic over the next few months. But I promise I’m still here! Photography and this community hold a very very special place in my heart, so as I get the hang of things, I hope to post more often.

Here’s a snapshot from this summer. This was one of those late nights I busied myself until the warmth of my halogen lamp was tinged by the day’s first blue hour. Perhaps I was delirious when I stepped outside, but it seemed the whole world was still—even more still than usual.
Happy new year, friends! Here’s to a wonderful 2023.
I am always asked if I sell prints, and the answer is yes! If you see a travel photo on my feed, it’s more than likely in the shop. Head to the link in my bio to browse through my favorites :)

Hello again, friends. Here’s a snapshot from a summer evening in Galveston

Hello! I’m back! (Again!) 

As the semester dies down, I thought I’d catch up with you all. My relationship with social media/this account has changed over the past few years, and frankly, I’ve enjoyed not chronicling my life on here the way I used to. But that doesn’t mean I’d like to distance myself completely! If anything, the time I’ve spent pursuing other endeavors has made me appreciate this particular expression of mine a little bit more. I’m excited to share what I’ve been up to!

Here are a few snapshots I’ve taken since April: 

2. Barton Springs, Austin

3. The view of campus from my freshman year dorm

4. A road trip to Lubbock for my cousin’s commencement ceremony 

5. A backpacking trip in Colorado

6. The nonprofit office I worked in over the summer

7. The corner of my first apartment 

That’s all for now! I have a lot of work I’ve been planning to share for a while, so stay tuned.

I was looking at photos from this trip to the Bay, and realized most of them are of the hills above the fog. Perhaps it’s its foreignness, or perhaps everyone enjoys being above the clouds, but the phenomena has always been entrancing
